data.title: Joseph by Andrew Kooman
data.meta_description: Joseph, a young man in his first year at Bible College is forced to come to terms with his mental illness. As Joseph's life unravels, he resists medical treatment with the desire to be healed by faith. Joseph's growing love for Becky, a girl from school and the one person committed to his wellness, is threatened by Cindy, his lifelong companion who both haunts and captivates his imagination. data.text:
Joseph, a young man in his first year at Bible College is forced to come to terms with his mental illness. As Joseph's life unravels, he resists medical treatment with the desire to be healed by faith. Joseph's growing love for Becky, a girl from school and the one person committed to his wellness, is threatened by Cindy, his lifelong companion who both haunts and captivates his imagination.

Year Printed: 2014

Running Time: 60 minutes

Acts: 1
